<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870410-0156 </DOCNO><HL> Brenda Sells Its 17% StakeIn Kerr Addison Mines Ltd.</HL><DD> 04/10/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> T.BND T.NOR T.KERTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> VANCOUVER  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Brenda Mines Ltd., 46% owned by Noranda Inc., Toronto, said it has sold its 17% interest in Kerr Addison Mines Ltd. to a group of underwriters for redistribution.    The selling price for the shares wasn't disclosed, but at the current market price of about $25.25 (Canadian) a share, the 2,830,390 shares would have a market value of about $71.5 million. The underwriting group is led by Wood Gundy Inc., Brenda Mines said.    The amount of any gain or loss on the sale will be reported in its quarterly financial statement, Brenda Mines said. It added that its investment in Kerr Addison has been carried on its balance sheet at about $64 million.    Brenda Mines said proceeds of the sale would be applied to eliminate the company's $32 million of debt and for general corporate purposes. </TEXT></DOC>